review_blob: Almost the perfect blend of malt and hops. The malts give it a round mouthfeel then the hops give it a bitter clean finish. This is one my my favorite beers.

This is the first beer Ive had from Lucid. Citrus hop aromas, with hits of malt sweetness. Mild citrus hop flavor, not very hoppy for an imperial IPA but it is well balanced. Overall I eally like this beer you dont  notice the alcohol is so high, it comes off very drinkable.

This beer is excellent. It has kind of a sweet roasted coffee and smokeon the nose, that continues in the flavor. There is also a sweet black licorice flavor that kind of lingers for minutes after you swallow. There isnt much alcohol flavor but you can deffinatley tell its in there.
Pours a clear bright yellow with a small white head. Has light hop aromas. Tast is crisp and bright, an excellent Pilsner
I get mero malt than hops in the aroma. An almost coppery metallic flavor with some citrusy hops on the finish. I am not a fan of this beer

Aromas are mostly pine hops but there is a little mwalt that can be detected. Tastes mostly like it smells, some malt but mostly piney hoppines although not as much as anticpated. Finishes with just a hint of alcohol but at 10%abv you can hardly tell, could be dangerous if you arent watching.

The nose is amazing, floral fruity hop aromas that jump right out of the glass. Bright copper color with a small white head. Nice malt backbone with a citrus hop flavor, not typical citrus maybe kind of a grassy citrus. Its alittle diffent but it is an excellent beer.
Fruity apricot flavors followed by  a slight hop bitterness. Bright orange color with a decent white head. Overall it was prety good not great
Bright orange color, citrus hop aromas. Flavors are mostly resinous grapefruit hops.
Lots of chocolate and coffe on the nose. Its very dark brown with a small tan head. Roasted malt flavors with hints of chocolate on the finish.

This beer has a kind of grassy, citrus aroma. It is medium bodied with not much carbonation. It doesnt have as much malt to it as I would have hoped and it really isnt all that hoppy either. I will definatley have to get a different sample but from this sample just purchased today I can only say it is slightly above average IPA.
UPDATED: MAR 28, 2012
Im not getting much aroma but it is a nice cooper color. Flavor is a pretty light roasted malt with a slight bitterness on the finish. Its a pretty good beer.

There are licorice, and alcohol aromas. It pours an almost black color with a very small tan head. The licorice continues in the flavor and it finishes kind of sweet with a woody character. Its a solid beer not as much bitter chocolate or coffee flavors as I usually like.

I got this because I relly like rye beers. It starts with a nice copper color but I dint get much from the nose a little bit from the hops but thats about it. Flavors ok some bitternes from the hops but I dont get much rye. All in all not bad but not great.

Has a bright fruit aroma as you wolud expect from this style. Nice deep red color. Flavors are strawberry more so than raspberry, not what I would have expected from the aromas. Als it finishes clean without as much sweetness as the aroma would suggest.
Nice pine aroma. Golden in color some lacing but not a ton, Has a great balanced bitter flavor. One of my favorite IPAs
UPDATED: JUL 6, 2012
Slightly malty aroma, copper/amber color. Sweet malty flavor with ahint of hops. Well balanced
Looks darker that it tastes. Has kind of a sour finish, takes some time to get used to but after the first few sips its okay.
Has good citrus hop flavor. A beautiful golden copper color, small white head. Overall a very good beer.
It has rosted malt aroma. It is very dark brown in color almost black. The body is lighter than youd expect from the color. The flavor is kind of light and nutty. Its good not great
